properties.documentation: Systém musí viesť evidenciu žiadostí o zriadenie vodovodnej prípojky.
Systém musí umožniť koncovému zákazníkovi zadať žiadosť o zriadenie vodovodnej prípojky.
Systém musí podporovať zriadenie prípojky pre osobu aj pre firmu.
Systém musí umožniť vybrať typ prípojky (vodovodná, odpadová) a typ spotrebiteľa (domácnosť, priemysel).
Systém musí umožniť zadať údaje o mieste dodávky (parcela, vlastník, oblasť) vrátane adresy.
Systém musí umožniť zadať kontaktné údaje: telefón a e-mail.
Systém musí umožniť priložiť ku žiadosti rôzne typy príloh: potvrdenie o trvalom pobyte, potvrdenie o vlastníctve nehnuteľnosti, kolaudačné rozhodnutie apod.
Systém musí vedieť zobraziť koncovému používateľovi zoznam ním podaných žiadostí.

Používateľ zadá informáciu o type prípojky.
Systém ponúka vodovodnú prípojku alebo kanalizačnú prípojku.
Používateľ zadá informácie o prípojnom mieste.
Systém kontroluje zadanie adresy.
Používateľ potvrdí zadané údaje.
Systém uloží údaje.
Systém vyzve používateľa na zadanie prílohy.
Používateľ vyberie prílohu z lokálneho úložiska.
Systém uloží prílohu.
Používateľ zadá názov, typ a prípadne popis prílohy.

Používateľ ukončí pridávanie príloh.
Systém umožní používateľovi vypísať informácie o firme (názov, IČO apod).
Používateľ zadá informácie o fime.

properties.documentation: The class holds address information.
The class represents a company in a list of companies. A company can be used as an applicant when submitting an application. Class responsibility is to hold information about one company.
The class represents a person in a list of persons. A person can be used as an applicant when submitting an application. Class responsibility is to hold information about one person.

It represents a person's birth number. The domain knows two types of birth numbers: valid and invalid. A valid birth number conforms to the birth number rules: it has the format 999999/9990. An invalid birth number is a meaningless identifier.
Phone or e-mail contact. Just a data holder.

The class represents data about the creation or updating data. The class supports the auditability of a record at the simplest level, i.e. when the record was created and when it was last updated. All attributes are always filled. The record creation attributes never change (created, createdBy). Class responsibility is to ensure that the correct information is consistently generated when the record is created or updated.

documentation.value: When the object is created, the time attributes (created, updated) are set to the current date and time. Attributes identifying the user (createdBy, updatedBy) are set to the value sent as parameter. The input parameter is mandatory.

The method creates a new RecordInfo object in which the user is consistently changed. The method preserves the information about the creation of the record (createdBy and created), but assigns the sent user and the current date and time to the update attributes of the record. The input parameter is mandatory.

properties.documentation: An interface represents a domain event. The implementation is responsible for providing domain event data.
The interface is used to send domain events. The implementation must ensure asynchronous sending of the message.
The interface serves to receive domain events. The implementation makes it possible to handle the domain event and takes care of an adequate response in the domain.

The class represents the applicant in the system, which can be a person or an organization. The class also records the contact of the applicant. Class responsibility is to ensure uniform access to the applicant, regardless of whether it is a person or a company. The class is responsible for the fact that the applicant is either a company or a person, never both at the same time or neither.

documentation.value: Updating contact information (e-mail, phone). If the input parameter is NULL, the method creates a contact with blank contact information.

properties.documentation: The class represents a single attachment. The attachment can be any document (DOC, PDF, JPG) that a user attaches to an entity. An example of an attachment is a confirmation of permanent residence in PDF format. Class responsibility is to hold a reference to the document together with the document metadata (name, description).

documentation.value: A link to a document stored on a separate data storage outside the database.

properties.documentation: The class represents a list of attachments to some entity - for example, to an application for the establishment of a water connection. Class responsibility is to ensure consistent appending and type uniqueness checking.

documentation.value: The method adds a new attachment to the list. The method returns TRUE if the new request attachment could be listed.
The method removes the attachment with the given ID from the list of attachments. The method returns TRUE if the remove was successful.

properties.documentation: Place of water connection installation. It contains more detailed information about the site, including the address.

The class represents an application for the approval of a water supply or sewerage connection. Class responsibility is to keep consistent information about the application, the applicant and the attached documents.

documentation.value: The method changes the contact to the requester. The method updates data on the last change of the WaterApplication record.

properties.documentation: A domain event that occurs when a WaterConnection object is created.
The event occurs when the attributes in the WaterConnection object change.
Type of connection: water or sewage.
Project status is information entered by the user.
Status list for the water connection application process.
For the type of water sewerage, an important differentiator is whether it is a household or an industry.

documentation.value: The attribute is a link in the company list to the applicant. The attribute is optional, if it is null, the "person" attribute must be filled.
The attribute is a link in the person list to the applicant. The attribute is optional, if it is null, the "company" attribute must be filled.
Phone or e-mail of the applicant. Mandatory.
Information about when and by whom the record was created and updated.
A link to a person or company with contact information.
